# reShkolo MVP Direction

## Product intent

- Build a web-first experience (opened via link/QR in browser), not an app-store product.
- Center student-to-teacher feedback while keeping the experience as serious and familiar as existing school systems.

## Space model

- Keep spaces flat: no single exclusive recipient or private owner.
- Allow invited participants on equal footing within a space.
- Students can invite teachers, principals, and parents.
- Invited teachers may also submit reflective feedback when invited.

## MVP input/output rules

- Feedback input supports only free text or speech.
- Do not introduce tags, numeric ratings, scoring, or threshold gates in MVP.
- Output consumed by participants is anonymous and aggregated.
- UI shows aggregated summary only (no raw feedback list in MVP).
- UI language is English.

## Aggregation pipeline constraints

- For voice submissions: transcribe speech to text first.
- Classify sentiment/type as praise (`похвала`) or critical remark (`забележка`).
- Run classification as a separate call from summary generation.
- Append each submission to the collective feedback pool.
- Generate updated aggregate summaries through LLM instructions.
- Aggregation prompts should prioritize constructive feedback and de-emphasize repetitive, low-information content.
- If aggregation fails, keep the submitted feedback (do not roll back the row).

## Scope boundaries

- Do not lock in final data schema in early MVP planning.
- Keep milestones and deeper architecture as separate planning steps.

## Implementation stack (decided)

- **Wasp** app; deploy with **Railway** (Postgres included). Start on free tier; upgrade when needed.
- **PostgreSQL** for durable data (not file-only storage).
- **Aggregation:** hosted LLM APIs only (target **Claude Opus**-class for quality); compare with cheaper/free API models in tests — **no self-hosted** LLM weights.
- **Speech-to-text:** hosted transcription API only (no self-hosted STT).
- **Aggregation:** hybrid in MVP — **sync classification** on submit, **async summary generation** in background.
- **Access/join:** anyone with app access can create a space; joining by short code is supported.
